{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Bless Yahweh, my soul. Yahweh, my God, you are very great."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You are clothed with honor and majesty."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He covers himself with light as with a garment. He stretches out the heavens like a curtain."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He lays the beams of his rooms in the waters. He makes the clouds his chariot."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He walks on the wings of the wind."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He makes his messengers winds, and his servants flames of fire."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He laid the foundations of the earth, that it should not be moved forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You covered it with the deep as with a cloak. The waters stood above the mountains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "At your rebuke they fled. At the voice of your thunder they hurried away."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The mountains rose, the valleys sank down,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to the place which you had assigned to them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have set a boundary that they may not pass over, that they don’t turn again to cover the earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He sends springs into the valleys. They run among the mountains."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They give drink to every animal of the field. The wild donkeys quench their thirst."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The birds of the sky nest by them. They sing among the branches."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He waters the mountains from his rooms. The earth is filled with the fruit of your works."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He causes the grass to grow for the livestock, and plants for man to cultivate,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "that he may produce food out of the earth:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "wine that makes the heart of man glad, oil to make his face to shine,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and bread that strengthens man’s heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh’s trees are well watered, the cedars of Lebanon, which he has planted,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "where the birds make their nests. The stork makes its home in the cypress trees."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The high mountains are for the wild goats. The rocks are a refuge for the rock badgers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He appointed the moon for seasons. The sun knows when to set."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You make darkness, and it is night, in which all the animals of the forest prowl."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The young lions roar after their prey, and seek their food from God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The sun rises, and they steal away, and lie down in their dens."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Man goes out to his work, to his labor until the evening."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, how many are your works! In wisdom, you have made them all."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The earth is full of your riches."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "There is the sea, great and wide, in which are innumerable living things,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "both small and large animals."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "There the ships go, and leviathan, whom you formed to play there."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "These all wait for you, that you may give them their food in due season."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You give to them; they gather. You open your hand; they are satisfied with good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You hide your face; they are troubled. You take away their breath; they die and return to the dust."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You send out your Spirit and they are created. You renew the face of the ground."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let Yahweh’s glory endure forever. Let Yahweh rejoice in his works."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He looks at the earth, and it trembles. He touches the mountains, and they smoke."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I will sing to Yahweh as long as I live. I will sing praise to my God while I have any being."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let my meditation be sweet to him. I will rejoice in Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let sinners be consumed out of the earth. Let the wicked be no more."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Bless Yahweh, my soul.\nPraise Yah!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}